narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned all about analyzing circuits at a very technical/detailed level. I additionally learned about different kinds of circuits and what their purpose was as well as the theory behind them.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course was interesting. The workload and labs were manageable and Professor Tang is a great lecturer. The textbook was a little hard, however, and hard to read because the chapters were so long. Also the labs were sometimes a little unorganized or did not work properly, however, the TAs and professor were very helpful and understanding in solving these problems.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Only take this course if it is a required class. It is so technical and in detail that it is only really helpful if it is required for your major.
